<statement><div><p>
A goblet is made up of a hemisphere mounted on top of a cylindrical base. The hemisphere has a radius of <m>{28} \,\text{m}</m>, and the cylindrical base has the same radius with a height of <m>{45} \,\text{m}</m>.</p>
<p>Answer the following:</p>
<ol type="i">
  <li><p>Find the <alert>total external surface area</alert> of the goblet.</p>
   <p><m>\text{Surface area}=</m><fillin characters="7" name="ans1"/><m>\,\text{m}^2</m></p>
    </li>
  <li><p>Determine the <alert>maximum volume of liquid</alert> the goblet can hold.</p>
   <p><m>\text{Volume}=</m><fillin characters="7" name="ans2"/><m>\,\text{m}^3</m></p>

    </li>
</ol></div></statement>
<solution><div><p><alert>Worked Solution</alert></p>

<p>
The goblet consists of two parts:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>a <alert>cylindrical base</alert></li>
  <li>a <alert>hemisphere on top</alert></li>
</ul>

<p>
From the question, the dimensions are:
<br/>
Radius of the hemisphere and cylinder = <m>{28}</m> m  
<br/>
Height of the cylindrical base = <m>{45}</m> m
</p>

<ol type="i">
  <li>
    <p><alert>Find the total external surface area of the goblet</alert></p>
    
    <p>
    Step 1: Curved surface area of the cylinder<br/>

    <md>
<mrow>\text{CSA of cylinder} \amp = 2 \pi r h</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = 2 \times \frac{22}{7} \times {28} \times {45}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {7920.0} \,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    Step 2: Curved surface area of the hemisphere<br/>

    <md>
<mrow>\text{CSA of hemisphere} \amp = 2 \pi r^2</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = 2 \times \frac{22}{7} \times ({28})^2</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {4928.0} \,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    Step 3: Total external surface area<br/>

    <md>
<mrow>\text{Total surface area} \amp = {7920.0} + {4928.0}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {12848.0} \,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <p><alert>Determine the maximum volume of liquid the goblet can hold</alert></p>
    
    <p>
    Step 1: Volume of the cylinder<br/>

    <md>
<mrow>V_{\text{cylinder}} \amp = \pi r^2 h</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{22}{7} \times ({28})^2 \times {45}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {110880} \,\text{m}^3</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    Step 2: Volume of the hemisphere<br/>

    <md>
<mrow>V_{\text{hemisphere}} \amp = \frac{2}{3} \pi r^3</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{2}{3} \times \frac{22}{7} \times ({28})^3</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {\frac{137984}{3}} \,\text{m}^3</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    Step 3: Total volume of goblet<br/>

    <md>
<mrow>V_{\text{total}} \amp = {110880} + {\frac{137984}{3}}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {156875} \,\text{m}^3</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
</div></solution>
<answer><p><m>12848</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>156875</m></p></answer>
